childNodes.textContent: Reviewed in the United States on February 28, 2024

Beautiful 95% tungsten cube with slightly beveled edges and corners.  The finish is very nice.  I can’t stop pranking myself by trying to pick it up with one hand.  It’s hilarious next to my 20 lb dumbbell which is half the weight and double the volume.  I am comforted knowing it will be my only possession to survive a forest fire.  Highly recommended 10/10.

attributes.class: a-size-base a-link-normal review-title a-color-base review-title-content a-text-bold

childNodes.textContent: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2021
My cube arrived carefully wrapped in a little bag, inside styrofoam packing, inside a sturdy wooden box, inside more styrofoam, inside a cardboard box that said "heavy".
And it precisely met expectations. It is a cube, a four inch cube, and apparently, tungsten.
It was heavy, so heavy that it felt unearthly, supernatural.  People have that reaction when handling tungsten, it is so heavy it just doesn't feel right.

I was impressed by the quality of construction and packaging. The cube is very nicely milled, rounded, and polished, or whatever you can do to work tungsten. It is a perfect flawless cube with perfectly done edges and surfaces. It comes with a certificate of authenticity and a brief scientific explanation. I can tell they put some effort into making and offering this.
In fact, I am so pleased that I have ordered several additional cubes in various smaller sizes. Highly recommended if you are rich, and a nerd… or the smaller ones if you are less of either.

Nice to use for display. Let your friends try to lift this deceivingly small cube

attributes.class: a-size-base a-link-normal review-title a-color-base review-title-content a-text-bold

childNodes.textContent: Crazy to pay $70 a pound for this 42 pound cube.
Reviewed in the United States on April 11, 2022

$70 a pound or about $5 an oz, and I hope it increases in value being a rare metal someday.  Can't pick it up with one hand without a glove on, two hands is heavy enough.  love that it is the same density as gold (more or less), and would be worth $1.3M if at gold value.  Fun to think about it being gold, makes you watch movies where they have gold bars and through them around like it is nothing.  Enjoy, think of it as an investment.

attributes.class: a-size-base a-link-normal review-title a-color-base review-title-content a-text-bold

childNodes.textContent: This tungsten cube is as advertised
Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023

I've been collecting tungsten cubes for nearly a decade and this is amongst the finest in my collection. My wife isn't too thrilled, but a guy has to have hobbies.  In fact, I had to reinforce my display shelf and add a support to our house's foundation to prevent unforeseen catastrophic events and to convey assurance to my neighbors, who were growing concerned about a depression forming around our residence. I plan to give them as holiday gifts this year.

childNodes.textContent: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2020

The 4 inch cube is described as amazingly heavy.  One could accurately say that's an understatement!  Best paper weight there is but you may have a bit of difficulty retrieving anyting under it. This could well be the most useless but most astounding and intriguing thing I've ever bought!  I doubt the amazement will ever wear off!
